-- Strong inflows boost Man Group's funds under management to $57.7 bln
-- By Nishant Kumar
-- Fri Aug 01, 2014 02:24AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 1 (Reuters) - Man Group's <EMG.L> funds under management rose 7 percent to $57.7 billion in the first half helped by net inflows of $2.8 billion, the London-listed hedge fund firm said on Friday.

Sales rose 91 percent to $12.4 billion in the first half as compared with the same period last year, while redemptions fell 17 percent to $9.6 billion, the money manager said, adding that it remained cautious heading into the second half of the year. Investment performance added $700 million in the first half.